From William M Everett Subject Re The earth also pollutes In article A Rodger C Scoggin writes In article DZVB B , William A Bacon says The Earth may spew alot of substances into the atmosphere, but the quality of your toxic output can easily make up for the lack of quantity Excuse me Quality As in grade A CO and grade B CO I may not have this quite right but I was under the impression that CO was CO Furthermore, the planet is a system of carbon, sulfur and other chemicals which have been acting for billions of years, we are but newcomers to the system we must adapt and control in order to bring about stability Also, two wrongs do not make a right, so continuing our practices despite overwhelming data is just ignorance in non action A There is no reason to believe this system is inherently stable The Ice ages occured without any help from humans B The point was that the human contribution of CO and other greenhouse gasses is insignificant and it won't really make a difference if we make more or less C What overwhelming data I see lots of 'projections' of the future, which is fascinating, considering they can't predict the weather two weeks in advance William Everett Tan, Rested, and ready Harvey Mudd College NIXON in ' These opinions are mine you can't have them